hopobject.body: A Second Class stamp celebrex 100 mg obat apa It was certainly the city that I had in my sights, when we first looked to export Green & Black’s. A small, pioneering eco-retailer, Katharine Tiddens at Terra Verde, pioneered our chocolate there, after spotting it at a German trade show – alongside organic cotton sheets, low-VOC paints, and natural mattresses. Back then, Sting & Trudie Styler would order their Christmas gift baskets through Terra Verde and we were ridiculously excited to be included. But the retailer I really wanted to see my chocolate on the shelves of was Dean & Deluca, which then had one small shop on Prince Street selling gourmet treats the like of which few had seen: fiddle-head ferns, wild garlic, sun-dried tomatoes (for those of us who remember life before sun-dried tomatoes…)
